{"parse":{"title":"doctor","pageid":8409,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Doctor}}\n==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|doctour||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:doctour|tree=1}}\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*deḱ-}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|doctor}}, {{m|enm|doctour||an expert, authority on a subject}}, from {{der|en|xno|doctour}}, from {{der|en|la|doctor||teacher}}, from {{m|la|doceō||to teach}}. Displaced native {{cog|enm|lerare||doctor, teacher}} (from {{cog|enm|leren||to teach, instruct}} from {{cog|ang|læran|lǣran, lēran|to teach, instruct, guide}}, compare {{cog|ang|lārēow||teacher, master}}). Displaced {{cog|ang|lǣċe||doctor, physician}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdɒktə(ɹ)/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdɑktɚ/|a=GA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdɔktə/|/ˈdɒktə/|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈdɒktəɹ/|a=CA}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-doctor.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-doctor.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-doctor.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɒktə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|doc|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q39631}} A [[physician]]; a [[member]] of the [[medical]] [[profession]]; one who is [[train]]ed and [[license]]d to [[heal]] the [[sick]] or [[injure]]d. The final [[examination]] and [[qualification]] may [[award]] a doctor [[degree]] in which case the [[post-nominal]] letters are [[w: Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine|DO]], [[DPM]], [[w:Doctor of Medicine|MD]], [[DMD]], or [[DDS]] in the [[US]], or [[MBBS]] or [[BDS]] in the [[UK]]. <!--Encyclopedic info: In the UK the qualifying exam is a first degree and the letters are [[MBBS]] or [[MBChB]]. (Usually refers to a [[general practitioner]], as others are referred to by their [[specialty|specialties]].)-->\n#: {{syn|en|physician<id:Q39631>|Thesaurus:physician}}\n#: {{hyper|en|person#Noun}}\n#: {{ux|en|If you still feel unwell tomorrow, see your '''doctor'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Cymbeline |V|v|passage=By medicine life may be prolonged, yet death / Will seize the '''doctor''' too.}}\n# A person who has attained a [[doctorate]], such as a [[Ph.D.]] or [[Th.D.]] or one of many other [[terminal degree]]s conferred by a [[college]] or [[university]].\n# A [[veterinarian]]; a medical [[practitioner]] who treats non-human [[animal]]s.\n# {{n-g|A [[nickname]] for a person who has special knowledge or talents to manipulate or arrange transactions.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[teacher]]; one skilled in a [[profession]] or a branch of knowledge; a learned man.\n#* {{RQ:Latimer Lords Prayer|chapter=[The First Sermon]|folio=5|verso=1|passage=So from that tyme forwarde I began to ſmell the word of god, and forſoke the ſchole '''doctors''' and ſuch foolries.}}\n#* {{RQ:Bacon Essayes|chapter=Of Goodness and Goodness of Nature|passage=one of the '''doctors''' of Italy, Nicholas Macciavel}}\n# {{lb|en|dated}} Any [[mechanical]] [[contrivance]] intended to remedy a difficulty or serve some purpose in an [[exigency]].\n#: ''the '''doctor''' of a calico-printing machine, which is a knife to remove superfluous colouring matter''\n#: ''the '''doctor''', or auxiliary engine, also called \"donkey engine\"''\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2010|author=Ramesh Bangia|title=Dictionary of Information Technology|page=172|passage=The use of a disk '''doctor''' may be the only way of recovering valuable data following a disk crash.}}\n# A fish, the [[friar skate]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[witchdoctor]].\n#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1937|year_published=1947|author={{w|Ion L. Idriess}}|title={{w|Over the Range (Idriess book)|Over the Range}}|publisher={{w|Angus and Robertson}}|location=Sydney|page=177|passage=[T]he material operation is that the '''doctor''' would catch a certain species of lizard under particular circumstances at a particular time. He would croon over it the name of the man while gently rattling his ‘devil bones,’ thus calling up the evil spirit that follows these particular charmed bones.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|nautical|slang}} A [[ship]]'s [[cook]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1844|author=William Robert Wilde|title=Narrative of a Voyage to Madeira, Teneriffe and Along the Shores of the Mediterranean|page=124\n|passage={{...}} old Scotch Jem the boatswain, tunes his fiddle, and the '''doctor''', (ship's cook,) produces his tambourine; the men dance on deck, {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1881|title=The United Service|volume=5|page=212\n|passage=His galley is small, and, microscopic as it is, it is shared by his brother in misery, the ship's cook, he whom the crew familiarly know as the “'''Doctor'''.”}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* '''[[Doctor]]''' is capitalized when used as a title:\n*: '''''Doctor''' Smith''\n* In the UK and Commonwealth (except Canada), a surgeon (including a dental or veterinary surgeon) is commonly addressed as Mr./Ms./Mrs. rather than Doctor.\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|physician}} {{l|en|doc}} {{qualifier|informal}}, [[family doctor]], [[general practitioner]], [[GP]] {{qualifier|UK}}, [[medic]], [[physician]], [[sawbones]] {{qualifier|slang}}, [[surgeon]] (''who undertakes surgery''); see also [[Thesaurus:physician]]\n* {{sense|veterinarian}} {{l|en|vet}}, {{l|en|veterinarian}}, {{l|en|veterinary}}, {{l|en|veterinary surgeon}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n''See also'' '''Types of academic doctor''' ''below''\n{{col|en|antidoctor|doctorable|doctorer|doctorese|doctorfish|doctorial|doctorlike|doctorling|dogtor|interdoctor|intradoctor|multidoctor|nondoctor|subdoctor|superdoctor|teledoctor|witchdoctor|resident doctor\n|an apple a day keeps the doctor away|Doctor Yellow\n|Angelic Doctor|brain doctor\n|barefoot doctor|abortion doctor|bedoctor|fish doctor\n|Cape Doctor| doctor's we|frankenstein doctor|Frankenstein doctor|Frankensteinian doctor|frankensteinian doctor\n|cleaning-doctor\n|clown doctor\n|color-doctor,colour-doctor\n|company doctor|doctor killer|rain doctor\n|couch doctor\n|dedoctor\n|doc\n|doctoral\n|doctor-assisted suicide\n|doctor blade\n|doctor-box\n|doctorcraft\n|doctordom|doctor's note\n|doctoress,doctress\n|doctor-fish\n|Doctor George Mountain\n|doctor-gum\n|doctorhead,doctorhood\n|doctorish\n|doctorishness\n|doctorism\n|doctorise,doctorize\n|doctorless\n|doctorly\n|Doctor Martens\n|Doctor of Divinity\n|Doctor of Law\n|Doctor of Letters\n|Doctor of Philosophy\n|Doctor of Science\n|Doctor of the Chair\n|Doctor of Veterinary Medicine\n|Doctors' Commons\n|doctor's curse|doctor's bonnet\n|Doctors Gap\n|doctor's gum\n|doctor-shears\n|doctorship\n|doctor's orders\n|Doctors of the Church\n|doctorspeak\n|doctor's stuff,doctor-stuff\n|Doctor Yellow\n|Dr,Dr.\n|family doctor\n|flying doctor\n|Fremantle Doctor\n|herb doctor\n|honorary doctor\n|horse-doctor\n|junior doctor\n|lint-doctor\n|mad-doctor\n|paradoctor\n|play doctor\n|quack doctor\n|rain-doctor\n|saw doctor\n|school doctor\n|snake doctor\n|spin doctor\n|under-doctor\n|underdoctored\n|under the doctor\n|undoctor\n|undoctored\n|water-doctor\n|what the doctor ordered,just what the doctor ordered\n|witch doctor\n|woman doctor\n|you are the doctor,you're the doctor\n|an apple a day keeps the doctor at bay|doctor bird|doctor shopping|doctor up|dog doctor|eye doctor|good doctor|head doctor|horse doctor|I am a doctor|is anyone here a doctor|kaffir doctor|lint doctor|medical doctor|obeah doctor|outfit doctor|plague doctor|rig doctor|root doctor|script doctor|spirit doctor|the good doctor|water doctor|doctor's certificate|doctor's office|pox doctor's clerk|priest-doctor}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|en|docent|doctorand|doctorate|doctrine|doctrix}}\n{{col-top|2|types of academic doctor}}\n* Doctor of Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine ([[D.A.O.M.]])\n* Doctor of Arts ([[D.A.]])\n* Doctor of Architecture ([[D.Arch.]])\n* Doctor of Applied Science ([[D.A.S.]])\n* Doctor of Business Administration ([[D.B.A.]])\n* Doctor of Chemistry ([[D.Chem.]])\n* Doctor of Chiropractic ([[D.C.]])\n* Doctor of Civil Law ([[D.C.L.]])\n* Doctor of Criminal Justice ([[D.C.J.]])\n* Doctor of Comparative/Civil Law ([[D.C.L.]])\n* Doctor of Computer Science ([[D.C.S.]])\n* Doctor of Criminology ([[D.Crim.]])\n* Doctor of Dental Medicine ([[D.M.D.]])\n* Doctor of Dental Surgery ([[D.D.S.]])\n* Doctor of Design ([[Dr.DES.]])\n* Doctor of Education ([[Ed.D.]])\n* Doctor of Environmental Design ([[D.E.D.]])\n* Doctor of Engineering ([[D.Eng.]])\n* Doctor of Environment ([[D.Env.]])\n* Doctor of Engineering Science ([[D.E.Sc.]]/[[Sc.D.E.]])\n* Doctor of Forestry ([[D.F.]])\n* Doctor of Fine Arts ([[D.F.A.]])\n* Doctor of Geological Science ([[D.G.S.]])\n* Doctor of Hebrew Literature/Letters ([[D.H.L.]])\n* Doctor of Health and Safety ([[D.H.S.]])\n* Doctor of Hebrew Studies ([[D.H.S.]])\n* Doctor of Industrial Technology ([[D.I.T.]])\n* Doctor of Information Technology ([[D.I.T.]])\n* Doctor of Juridical Science ([[S.J.D.]])\n* Doctor of Library Science ([[D.L.S.]])\n* Doctor of Music ([[D.M.]])\n* Doctor of Musical Arts ([[D.M.A.]], [[A.Mus.D.]])\n* Doctor of Musical Education ([[D.M.E.]])\n* Doctor of Ministry ([[D.Min.]]/[[D.M.]])\n* Doctor of Modern Languages ([[D.M.L.]])\n* Doctor of Music Ministry ([[D.M.M.]])\n* Doctor of Medical Science ([[D.M.Sc.]])\n* Doctor of Nursing Science ([[D.N.Sc.]])\n* Doctor of Public Administration ([[D.P.A.]])\n* Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine ([[D.O.]])\n* Doctor of Pharmacy ([[Pharm.D.]])\n* Doctor of Philosophy ([[Ph.D.]])\n* Doctor of Physical Education ([[D.P.E.]])\n* Doctor of Physical Therapy ([[D.P.T.]])\n* Doctor of Podiatric Medicine ([[D.P.M.]])\n* Doctor of Psychology ([[Psy.D.]])\n* Doctor of Public Health ([[D.P.H.]])\n* Doctor of Professional Studies ([[D.P.S.]])\n* Doctor of Religious Education ([[D.R.E.]])\n* Doctor of Recreation ([[D.Rec.]]/[[D.R.]])\n* Doctor of Science ([[D.Sc.]]/[[Sc.D.]])\n* Doctor of Science in Dentistry ([[D.Sc.D.]])\n* Doctor of Science and Hygiene ([[D.Sc.H.]])\n* Doctor of Science in Veterinary Medicine ([[D.Sc.V.M.]])\n* Doctor of Sacred Music ([[D.S.M.]])\n* Doctor of Social Science ([[D.S.Sc.]])\n* Doctor of Social Work ([[D.S.W.]])\n* Doctor of Canon Law ([[J.C.D.]])\n* Doctor of the Science of Law ([[L.Sc.D.]])\n* Doctor of Rehabilitation ([[Rh.D.]])\n* Doctor of Sacred Theology ([[S.T.D.]])\n* Doctor of Science ([[D.Sc.]])\n* Doctor of Technology ([[D.Tech.]])\n* Doctor of Theology ([[Th.D.]])\n* Doctor of the University ([[D.Univ]])\n* Doctor of Veterinary Medicine or Veterinary Medical Doctor ([[D.V.M.]]/[[V.M.D]])\n* Divinitatis Doctor, Doctor of Divinity ([[D.D.]])\n* Juris Doctor, Doctor of Law ([[J.D.]])\n* Optometry Doctor, Doctor of Optometry ([[O.D.]])\n* Legum Doctor, Doctor of Laws ([[LL.D.]])\n* Literarum Doctor, Doctor of Letters ([[D.Litt.]])\n* Medicine Doctor, Doctor of Medicine ([[M.D.]]/[[D.M.]])\n* Music Doctor, Doctor of Music ([[D.Mus.]])\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{col-top|2|desc}}\n* {{desc|srn|datra}}\n* {{desc|tpi|dokta}}\n* {{desc|bn|ডাক্তার|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|kxd|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ceb|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|prs|داکتر|tr=dâktar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ee|ɖɔkta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ha|doktā̀|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|he|דוקטור|tr=dóktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|haw|kauka|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hi|डॉक्टर|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ln|dɔkɔtɔ́lɔ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|uvl|dokta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|luo|dokta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ml|ഡോക്റ്റർ|bor=1|alts=1}}\n* {{desc|mi|tākuta|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mkj|doahksoa|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ne|डाक्टर|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sid|doktorichcha|bor=1|der=1}}\n* {{desc|sw|daktari|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ta|டாக்டர்|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|th|ดอกเตอร์|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|unm|ntaktël|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ur|ڈاکٹر|tr=ḍākṭar|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|doctor|bor=1}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|person who has attained a doctorate}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t|af|doktor}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|دُكْتُور|m}} or {{t|ar|دُكْتُورَة|f}}, {{t|ar|طَبِيب|m}} or {{t|ar|طَبِيبَة|f}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|دكتور|m|tr=duktūr}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|دكتور|m|tr=doktōr}}, {{t|acw|دكتورة|f|tr=doktōra}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܕܘܿܟ݂ܬܘܿܪ|m}}, {{t|aii|ܕܘܿܟ݂ܬܘܿܪܬܵܐ|f}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|դոկտոր}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|doutor|m}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|doktor}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|табип}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|до́ктар|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|до́ктор|m}}, {{t|bg|до́кторка|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t+|yue|博士|tr=bok3 si6}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|博士|tr=bóshì}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|doktor|m}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|doktor|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|doctor|m|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|doktoro}}, {{t|eo|virdoktoro}} {{q|male}} {{t|eo|doktorino}} {{q|female}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|tohtori}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|docteur|m}}, {{t+|fr|docteure|f}}, {{t+|fr|docteuse|f}}, {{t+|fr|doctoresse|f}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|doutor|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|დოქტორი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Doktor|m}}, {{t+|de|Doktorin|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|διδάκτορας|m|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|דוֹקטוֹר|m|tr=dóktor}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|डॉक्टर|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|doktor}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|læknir|m}}, {{t+|is|doktor|m}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|doktoro}}, {{t+|io|doktorulo}} {{q|male}}, {{t+|io|doktorino}} {{q|female}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|doktor}}\n* Irish: {{t+|ga|dochtúir|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|dottore|m}}, {{t+|it|dottoressa|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|博士|tr=はくし, hakushi, はかせ hakase}}\n* Kashmiri: {{t|ks|طبِیٖب/ڈَاکٹر}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|доктор}}, {{t|kk|доқтыр}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|បណ្ឌិត}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|박사(博士)}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|دکتۆر}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|доктор}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|doktors|m}}, {{t|lv|doktore|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|daktaras|m}}, {{t|lt|daktarė|f}}\n* Lombard: {{t|lmo|dutur}}\n* Luo: {{t|luo|dokta}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|доктор}}, {{t|mk|докторка|f}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|doktor}} {{q|Malaysia, Singapore}}, {{t+|ms|dokter}} {{q|Indonesia incl. Riau}}\n* Maltese: {{t|mt|dottor|m}}, {{t|mt|dottoressa|f}}\n* Manx: {{t|gv|olloo}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|डॉक्टर|m}}\n* Nengone: {{t|nen|dokita}}\n* Niuean: {{t|niu|ekekafo}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|docteu|m}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|دکتر|tr=doktor}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|doktor|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|doutor|m}}, {{t+|pt|doutora|f}}, {{t+|pt|doutorado|m}}, {{t|pt|doutorada|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|doctor|m|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|до́ктор|m|f}} {{q|male or female}}, {{t+|ru|до́кторша|f}} {{q|colloquial for female doctors, nonstandard}}\n* Sami:\n*: Skolt Sami: {{t|sms|dåhttar}}\n* Savosavo: {{t|svs|dokta}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|ollamh|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|до̏ктор|m}}, {{t|sh|до̏кторица|f}}, {{t|sh|до̏кто̄рка|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|dȍktor|m}}, {{t+|sh|dȍktorica|f}}, {{t|sh|dȍktōrka|f}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|dutturi|m}}, {{t|scn|dutturissa|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|doktor|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|doktor|m}}, {{t|sl|doktorica|f}}\n* Southern Altai: {{t|alt|доктор}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|doctor|m}}, {{t+|es|doctora|f}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|daktari}}, {{t|sw|dokta}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|doktor}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|paham}}, {{t+|tl|doktor}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|доктор}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|டாக்டர்}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|డాక్టర్}}, {{t+|te|డాక్టరు}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|ดอกเตอร์}}, {{t+|th|ดุษฎีบัณฑิต}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|doktor}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|doktor}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|до́ктор|m}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|ntaktël}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|دوكتور}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|doktor}}\n* Venetan: {{t|vec|dotor|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|tiến sĩ}} ({{t|vi|進士}})\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|dokan}}, {{t|vo|hidokan}} {{q|male}}, {{t|vo|jidokan}} {{q|female}}, {{t|vo|dokel}}, {{q|older term, obsolete}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|docteur|m}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|דאָקטאָר|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{trans-see|medical doctor|physician}}\n{{trans-see|veterinarian}}\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Sardinian: {{t-check|sc|duttore|m}}\n* Telugu: {{t-check|te|వైధ్యుడు}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col|en\n|preceptor\n|proctor\n|professor\n}}\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{pedia}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To act as a medical [[#Noun|doctor]] to.\n#: {{ux|en|Her children '''doctored''' her back to health.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|humorous}} To act as a medical [[#Noun|doctor]].\n#* '''2017''', \"Do No Harm\", season 8, episode 2 of ''{{w|Adventure Time}}''\n#*: Doctor Princess: Put this on. [''gives her lab coat to Finn''] OK, you're a doctor now. Good luck.\n#*: Finn: Wait, wait, whoa, whoa, whoa, wait! I don't know how to '''doctor'''!\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make (someone) into an (academic) [[#Noun|doctor]]; to [[confer]] a [[doctorate]] upon.\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[physically]] [[alter]] ([[medically]] or [[surgically]]) a living being in order to change [[growth]] or [[behavior]].\n#: {{ux|en|They '''doctored''' their apple trees by vigorous pruning, and now the dwarfed trees are easier to pick.}}\n#: {{ux|en|We may legally '''doctor''' a pet to reduce its libido.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[genetically]] [[alter]] an [[extant]] [[species]].\n#: {{ux|en|Mendel's discoveries showed how the evolution of a species may be '''doctored'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|figurative}} To [[alter]] or make [[obscure]], as with the intention to [[deceive]], especially a [[document]].\n#: {{ux|en|To '''doctor''' the signature of an [[instrument]] with intent to defraud is an example of [[forgery]].}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en-GB|author=Edward Helmore|title=How a picture came to symbolize the Prince Andrew sexual abuse case|work=The Guardian|date=2022-02-15|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2022/feb/15/virginia-giuffre-prince-andrew-picture-settlement-lawsuit|issn=0261-3077|passage=That picture – the one that Andrew claimed on BBC’s Newsnight might have been '''doctored''', since he had “no recollection” of then or ever meeting Giuffre at Tramp nightclub in London – will likely serve as both a prequel and postscript of the saga.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en-US|author=Mark Landler|title=Princess of Wales Apologizes, Saying She Edited Image|work=The New York Times|date=2024-03-11|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/11/world/europe/princess-kate-middleton-photo-edit-apology.html|issn=0362-4331|author2=Lauren Leatherby|passage=Catherine, the Princess of Wales, apologized on Monday for '''doctoring''' a photo of her with her three children, which was recalled by several news agencies on Sunday after they determined the image had been manipulated.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[adulterate]], [[drug]]{{,}} or [[poison]] (drink).\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1914|author=Ernest Bramah|title=Max Carrados\n|passage=There is no doubt that a few months ago Creake deliberately planned to poison her with some weed-killer. {{...}} The gist of it was that she had the strongest suspicion that Creake '''doctored''' a bottle of stout which he expected she would drink for her supper when she was alone.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|obsolete}} To take [[medicine]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|misdoctor}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|act as a medical doctor to}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|леку́вам}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᎧᏅᏫᎠ}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|doktorere}}\n* German: {{t+|de|verarzten}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|θεραπεύω}}, {{t+|el|γιατρεύω}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ἰατρεύω}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|curare}}, {{t+|it|medicare}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|មើល}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|îngriji}}, {{t+|ro|doctori}}, {{t+|ro|trata}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|лечи́ть|impf}}, {{t+|ru|врачева́ть|impf}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|daktari}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|award the title of doctor to}}\n* German: {{t|de|doktorieren}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|addottorare}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|doctorar}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|alter or make obscure, in order to deceive}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|篡改|tr=cuàngǎi}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|falzifikovat}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|forfalske}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|dokteren}}, {{t|nl|valsificeren}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|tohtoroida}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|falsifier}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|αλλοιώνω}}, {{t+|el|νοθεύω}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|afbaka}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|adulterare}}, {{t+|it|falsificare}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|改竄|tr=kaizan}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|fabrykować|impf}}, {{t+|pl|fałszować|impf}}, {{t+|pl|falsyfikować|impf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|adulterar}}\n* Romagnol: {{t|rgn|adulterêr}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|falsifica}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|фальсифици́ровать|impf}}, {{t+|ru|сфальсифици́ровать|pf}}, {{t+|ru|подде́лывать|impf}}, {{t+|ru|подде́лать|pf}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|adulterar}}\n* Swedish: {{t|sv|fiffla med}}, {{t+|sv|manipulera}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|surgeon}}\n\n{{C|en|Healthcare occupations|People}}\n\n==Asturian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|ast|:bor|es:doctor}}\n{{bor+|ast|es|doctor}}, compare native {{l|ast|doutor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{ast-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ast-noun|m|doctores}}\n\n# {{alt form|ast|doutor}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|ca|:bor|la:doctor}}\n{{bor+|ca|la|doctor|doctōrem}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA|[ó(r)]}}<!-- per GDLC and DCVB -->\n* {{audio|ca|LL-Q7026 (cat)-Marvives-doctor.wav|a=Barcelona}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ca-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# {{l|en|doctor}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|ca|doctoral}}\n* {{l|ca|doctorat}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n* {{R:ca:GDLC}}\n* {{R:ca:DNV}}\n* {{R:ca:DCVB}}\n\n==Chavacano==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|cbk|es|doctor||doctor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cbk-IPA}}\n* {{hyph|cbk|doc|tor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cbk-noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|doctor}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|nl|:inh|dum:doctor<ety:der<la:doctor>>}}\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|doctor}}, from {{der|nl|la|doctor||teacher, instructor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈdɔk.tɔr/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-doctor.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|doc|tor}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|ɔktɔr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-:en,-s|+}}\n\n# {{l|en|doctor}} (person who has attained a [[doctorate]])\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|nl|dr.}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|nl|doctorandus}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|af|doktor}}\n* {{desc|id|doktor|bor=1}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|nl|dokter}}\n\n==Latin==\n{{was fwotd|la|2013|November|23}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|la|title=doctor|:af|doceō<t:to teach>|-tor|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA|doctor}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{la-noun|doctor<3>|f=doctrīx/doctorissa}}\n\n# [[teacher]], [[instructor]]\n#* {{Q|la|Lucretius|De rerum natura|5|1310|thru=1312|quote={{...}} et validos partim prae se misere leones<br />cum '''doctoribus''' armatis saevisque magistris<br />qui moderarier his possent vinclisque tenere,|trans={{...}} and some let out before them strong lions,<br />with armed '''trainers''' and fierce masters<br />to manage them and hold them in restraints,}}\n# {{lb|la|Ecclesiastical Latin}} [[catechist]], Doctor of the Church\n\n====Declension====\n{{la-ndecl|doctor<3>}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|la|doctōrō}} {{q|Mediaeval}}\n* {{l|la|doctrīna}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col4|la\n|doceō\n|docibilis\n|docibilitās\n|docilis\n|docilitās\n|doctē\n|doctificus\n|doctiusculē\n|doctrīnālis\n|doctus\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|egl|dutåur}}\n* {{desc|fur|dotôr}}\n* Italo-Dalmatian\n** {{desc|dlm|dotuar}}\n** {{desc|it|dottore}}\n** {{desc|scn|dutturi}}\n** {{desc|mt|dottor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|roa-opt|doutor}}\n** {{desc|gl|doutor}}\n** {{desc|pt|doutor}}\n* {{desc|sc|duttore|datori}}\n* {{desc|es|doutor}}\n* {{desctree|vec|dotor}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n; Borrowed terms\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|sq|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ar|دُكْتُور|tr=doktōr, duktūr|bor=1}}\n*: {{desc|arz|دُكْتُور|tr=duktūr}}\n*: {{desc|acw|دُكْتور|tr=duktōr}}\n* {{desc|hy|դոկտոր|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ast|doctor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|be|доктар|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bg|доктор|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ca|doctor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ckb|دکتۆر|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cs|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|et|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fo|doktari|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ka|დოქტორი|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|de|Doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nds-de|Dokter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hu|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|is|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|id|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ga|dochtúir|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lb|Dokter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|dum|doctor|bor=1}}\n** {{desctree|nl|doctor}}\n** {{desctree|nl|dokter}}\n** {{desc|li|dókter}}\n* {{desc|lv|doktors|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lt|daktaras|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mk|доктор|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nb|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nn|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|fro|doctur|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|zlw-ocs|doktor|lbor=1}}\n* {{desctree|zlw-opl|doktor|lbor=1}}\n* {{desc|ru|до́ктор|bor=1}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|stq|Dokter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sh|doktor|bor=1}} / {{l|sh|доктор}}\n* {{desc|sk|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sl|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|es|doctor|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|sv|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|uk|доктор|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|wym|dökter|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|doethur|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|yi|דאָקטאָר|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:la:L&S}}\n* {{R:la:Elementary Lewis}}\n* {{R:la:du Cange}}\n* {{R:la:Gaffiot}}\n* {{R:la:NLW}}\n\n{{C|la|Occupations|Education}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|ro|doftor||popular}}\n* {{alt|ro|dohtor|doptor|dostor||regional|or|archaic}}\n* {{alt|ro|доктор||post-1930s (Moldovan) Cyrillic spelling}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|ro|:bor|fr:docteur|de:Doktor}}\nBorrowed from {{der|ro|la|doctor}} (17th c.), via {{bor|ro|fr|docteur}} or {{bor|ro|de|Doktor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|/ˈdok.tor/}}\n* {{audio|ro|LL-Q7913 (ron)-Andreea Teodoraa-doctor.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|m|doctori|f=doctoriță|f2=doctoră|f2_qual=nonstandard|f3=doctoreasă|f3_qual=archaic}}\n\n# {{l|en|doctor}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-m}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|ro|medic}}\n\n{{C|ro|Occupations}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|es|Dr.|dostor|dotor}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|es|:bor|la:doctor}}\n{{bor+|es|la|doctor}}, compare native {{l|es|doutor}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|+<audio:LL-Q1321 (spa)-AdrianAbdulBaha-doctor.wav<a:Colombia>>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|f=+}}\n\n# {{l|en|doctor}} {{gl|Ph.D.}}\n# [[physician]]\n#: {{syn|es|médico}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|es|doctorado|doctorante}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|tl|doktor|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|yaq|takter|bor=1}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{C|es|Healthcare occupations}}"}}